defaultThe IEA is an intergovernmental organisation which acts as energy policy advisor to 28 member countries in their effort to ensure reliable, affordable and clean energy for their citizens. It is committed to promoting the “Three E’s” of balanced energy policy making: energy security, economic development and environmental protection. The United Kingdom has been a member country of the IEA since it was formed in 1974.
